  <h3>3. How to Find Keywords – Free Tools & Step‑by‑Step Process</h3>
  <p>You do not need expensive tools. Start with these free methods – they work for Kenyan websites.</p>
  
  <h4>Step 1: Mine Google Autocomplete (Instant Keyword Ideas)</h4>
  <p>Open Google Kenya (google.co.ke). Start typing a seed keyword (e.g., “best restaurant”) and note the suggestions. Then add a space and type a letter (e.g., “best restaurant a”, “best restaurant b”) to get more variations. Do this for your main services and locations.</p>
  <p><strong>Example seed keywords for a Nairobi plumber:</strong> “emergency plumber”, “plumber near me”, “how to fix”, “cost of plumber”. Each will generate dozens of long‑tail keyword ideas.</p>
  
  <h4>Step 2: Use “People Also Ask” (PAA) Boxes</h4>
  <p>Search for your seed keyword on Google. Scroll down to the “People also ask” section. Each question is a voice‑optimized keyword. Click on a question – more questions appear. Extract at least 20 PAA questions per topic.</p>
  
  <h4>Step 3: Analyze Competitor Keywords (Free)</h4>
  <p>Identify your top 3 competitors in Google search. Visit their websites. Look at their page titles, H1 tags, and the content. What phrases do they repeat? Use a free tool like <strong>Keyworddit</strong> (Reddit keyword extractor) or simply scan their meta keywords (view page source). For advanced free, use <strong>Google Keyword Planner</strong> (requires a free Google Ads account).</p>
  
  <h4>Step 4: Use AnswerThePublic (3 Free Searches Per Day)</h4>
  <p>Go to <strong>answerthepublic.com</strong>. Enter a keyword like “SEO Nairobi”. It generates hundreds of question‑based and preposition‑based keywords (near, for, with, without). Each is a potential voice query. Use your 3 free searches wisely.</p>
  
  <h4>Step 5: Google Search Console – Your Own Data</h4>
  <p>If you already have Search Console installed, go to Performance → Queries. Sort by impressions. Look for phrases that are already bringing traffic – those are your existing keyword assets. Optimize those pages further. Also look for queries with high impressions but low clicks – improve your title and meta description for those.</p>
  
  <h4>Step 6: Add Swahili and Sheng Variations</h4>
  <p>Use Google Translate or a native speaker to translate your main keywords. Examples:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>“Best phone repair near me” → “Ukarabati wa simu bora karibu nami”</li>
    <li>“Affordable house for rent” → “Nyumba ya kukodi bei rahisi”</li>
    <li>“Fast food delivery” → “Uwasilishaji wa chakula cha haraka”</li>
  </ul>
  <p>These have almost zero competition. Even if search volume is low, ranking for 10 Swahili phrases can bring you unique customers that competitors ignore.</p>

